    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Group portraits, usually paintings, representing members of the civil militia or civic guard. The genre was common in the Netherlands of the 16th and 17th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
